<subSubSection id="AA825DF16E405B57FF45FC667CCAC79E" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E2270E7A6E405B57FF45FC667C18C43B" blockId="1.[151,1436,901,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="D0ECD2686E405B57FF45FC667F34C3EB" bold="true" box="[197,332,941,967]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Etymology</emphasis>
: Named Angela after my beloved wife Angela Schmidt Lourenço Rodrigues – and 
<emphasis id="D0ECD2686E405B57FAC6FC667BECC3EA" box="[1350,1428,941,966]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">agrion</emphasis>
, neuter form of 
<emphasis id="D0ECD2686E405B57FECAFC1E7FEDC3C2" box="[330,405,981,1006]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">agrios</emphasis>
meaning &quot;wild&quot;, which in damselflies is now used as an indicator that a genus belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="259875F96E405B57FF60FC367C23C43B" authority="(Fliedner 2006)" baseAuthorityName="Fliedner" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[224,603,1021,1047]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Coenagrionidae (
<bibRefCitation id="8609738B6E405B57FE29FC367C2BC43B" author="Fliedner, H." box="[425,595,1021,1047]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" pagination="5 - 23" refId="ref4010" refString="Fliedner, H. (2006) Die wissenschaftlichen Namen der Libellen in Burmeisters' Handbuch der Entomologie. Virgo, 9, 5 - 23." type="journal article" year="2006">Fliedner 2006</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E2270E7A6E405B57FF46FBEE7C9FC44B" blockId="1.[151,1436,901,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="D0ECD2686E405B57FF46FBEE7C2BC413" bold="true" box="[198,595,1061,1087]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Generic characterization. Head</emphasis>
. Frons angulated in profile; pale postocular spots present; most posterior point of head at compound eyes (
<figureCitation id="7AA312FF6E405B57FDCEFB867CD1C44B" box="[590,681,1101,1127]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1155,1179]" captionTargetBox="[181,1402,466,1117]" captionTargetId="figure-435@2.[169,1417,437,1129]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Angelagrion fredericoi sp. nov. Color pattern (male holotype): a—lateral view; b—dorsal view; c—venter of metathorax; d—metapretarsus." pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Figs. 1a</figureCitation>
– 
<figureCitation id="7AA312FF6E405B57FD3CFB867CA1C44B" box="[700,729,1101,1127]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1692,1716]" captionTargetBox="[192,1384,934,1649]" captionTargetId="figure-340@4.[188,1398,917,1666]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Angelagrion nathaliae sp. nov. Color pattern (female holotype): a—lateral view; b—dorsal view; c—venter of metathorax." pageId="1" pageNumber="24">3a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E2270E7A6E405B57FF46FBBE7DBDC586" blockId="1.[151,1436,901,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="D0ECD2686E405B57FF46FBBE7F5BC4A3" bold="true" box="[198,291,1141,1167]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Thorax</emphasis>
. Posterior lobe of prothorax approximately rectangular and slightly trilobed, and mesostigmal plates triangular in both sexes (
<figureCitation id="7AA312FF6E405B57FD89FB567CFEC49B" box="[521,646,1181,1207]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,255,683,707]" captionTargetBox="[197,1349,439,657]" captionTargetId="figure-385@6.[188,1398,397,667]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Posterior lobe of prothorax: a—Angelagrion fredericoi sp. nov. – male; b—Angelagrion fredericoi sp. nov. – female; c—Angelagrion nathaliae sp. nov. – female." pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Figs. 5a–c</figureCitation>
); hind margin of interlaminal sinus prominent, meeting mid-dorsal carina at an obtuse angle; mid-dorsal carina narrowed before interlaminal sinus. Wings petiolated at or slightly before CuP (
<figureCitation id="7AA312FF6E405B57FEAFFB267FC9C52B" box="[303,433,1261,1287]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,255,1304,1328]" captionTargetBox="[288,1245,191,1259]" captionTargetId="figure-276@5.[228,1358,179,1296]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Angelagrion sp.. Wings: a—Angelagrion fredericoi sp. nov.; b—Angelagrion nathaliae sp. nov." pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Figs. 4a–b</figureCitation>
); CuP reaching CuP&amp;AA or posterior margin of wing; CuA extending for 3–7 cells posterior to vein descending from subnodus; 3–4 cells between quadrangle and vein descending from subnodus in Fw; RP 
<quantity id="2560A39F6E405B57FEBFFA867F1EC57B" box="[319,358,1341,1371]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" unit="in" value="2.0">
<subScript id="7E1C0C3F6E405B57FEBFFA867F3FC577" attach="left" box="[319,327,1357,1371]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">2</subScript>
in
</quantity>
Fw beginning slightly beyond Px 4–5 and in Hw at Px 4; pt costal side 3 times longer than distal side (
<figureCitation id="7AA312FF6E405B57FEA2FAA37FDBC5AE" box="[290,419,1384,1410]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,255,1304,1328]" captionTargetBox="[288,1245,191,1259]" captionTargetId="figure-276@5.[228,1358,179,1296]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Angelagrion sp.. Wings: a—Angelagrion fredericoi sp. nov.; b—Angelagrion nathaliae sp. nov." pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Figs. 4a–b</figureCitation>
), distal and proximal sides of pt subequal. Spurs on distal half of metafemur shorter than width of femur; metatibial spurs shorter than intervening spaces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E2270E7A6E405B57FF46FA737ABCC6C6" blockId="1.[151,1436,901,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="D0ECD2686E405B57FF46FA737F38C5FE" bold="true" box="[198,320,1464,1490]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Abdomen</emphasis>
. In both sexes mostly blue with black markings; S2–5 or S2–6 with a black mid-dorsal stripe terminating in an angulated expansion joined or not with the black apical annulus, which is expanded basally at varying degrees; S8–10 dark brown to black; sternum of S 
<quantity id="2560A39F6E405B57FC06F9C37DCFC60E" box="[902,951,1544,1570]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.032" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" unit="in" value="8.0">8 in</quantity>
males with a circular bluish-white spot (unique for genus). Male cercus dark, in lateral view much shorter than S10, approximately rounded; male paraproct entire, in lateral view about twice the length of cercus (
<figureCitation id="7AA312FF6E405B57FC2AF9937A7BC65E" box="[938,1027,1624,1650]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1430,1454]" captionTargetBox="[184,1388,797,1398]" captionTargetId="figure-390@6.[169,1417,762,1437]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Angelagrion fredericoi sp. nov.: a—Anal appendages – lateral view; b—Anal appendages – posterior view; c—Anal appendages and S8–10 – ventral view; d—S8–10 of female; Angelagrion nathaliae sp. nov.: e—S8–10 of female." pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Fig. 6a</figureCitation>
). Female S8 lacking vulvar spine; female cercus much shorter than S10; tergum of S10 with a very short dorso-posterior cleft. Ovipositor robust and long, with a single row of teeth along ventral margin of outer valves, and tip (excluding stylus) extending to tip of cerci (
<figureCitation id="7AA312FF6E405B57FEC4F91B7FBBC6C6" box="[324,451,1744,1770]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1430,1454]" captionTargetBox="[184,1388,797,1398]" captionTargetId="figure-390@6.[169,1417,762,1437]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Angelagrion fredericoi sp. nov.: a—Anal appendages – lateral view; b—Anal appendages – posterior view; c—Anal appendages and S8–10 – ventral view; d—S8–10 of female; Angelagrion nathaliae sp. nov.: e—S8–10 of female." pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Figs. 6d–e</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of S9 of female without denticles (
<figureCitation id="7AA312FF6E405B57FBB8F91B7AC0C6C6" box="[1080,1208,1744,1770]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1430,1454]" captionTargetBox="[184,1388,797,1398]" captionTargetId="figure-390@6.[169,1417,762,1437]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Angelagrion fredericoi sp. nov.: a—Anal appendages – lateral view; b—Anal appendages – posterior view; c—Anal appendages and S8–10 – ventral view; d—S8–10 of female; Angelagrion nathaliae sp. nov.: e—S8–10 of female." pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Figs. 6d–e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E2270E7A6E405B57FF46F9337CCAC79E" blockId="1.[151,1436,901,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
Male genital ligula with portion of distal segment distal to flexure gradually narrowing to a narrow, slightly spatulate apex about as wide as 0.25 of portion proximal to flexure; ental surface of distal segment with small sclerotized spines arranged in three groups; inner fold prominent, broad at base, as long as 0.70 of portion distal to flexure, and as wide as portion proximal to flexure; terminal fold present but small, its medial portion notched (
<figureCitation id="7AA312FF6E405B57FEDFF8537FA6C79E" box="[351,478,1944,1970]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="7.[151,255,954,978]" captionTargetBox="[204,1349,219,888]" captionTargetId="figure-138@7.[169,1417,197,928]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 7. Angelagrion fredericoi sp. nov. Genital ligula: a—ectal view; b—lateral view; c—ectal view with distal segment extended; d—lateral view with distal segment extended; e—detail of the junction of distal segment with inner fold showing sclerotized spines." pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Figs. 7a–e</figureCitation>
). Larva unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AA825DF16E405B54FF46F80B7F18C156" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E2270E7A6E405B54FF46F80B7F18C156" blockId="1.[151,1436,901,2010]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,152,378]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="D0ECD2686E405B57FF46F80B7F46C7F6" bold="true" box="[198,318,1984,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="259875F96E405B57FED0F80B7F9AC7F5" authorityName="Lencioni" authorityYear="2008" box="[336,482,1984,2009]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Angelagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D0ECD2686E405B57FED0F80B7F9AC7F5" box="[336,482,1984,2009]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Angelagrion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
